verbose_text: A key enzyme of RAS, angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) then converts Ang I into the biological active octapeptide, Ang II, which preferentially binds to its receptors, Ang II type 1 receptor (AT1R) or Ang II type 2 receptor (AT2R).
